OL,3,CHigh cost of living 'main reason' for
OL,4,CJersey's low birth rate
OL,6,F"If things were different I would have
OL,7,Fgiven my daughter a little brother or
OL,8,Fsister."
OL,10,FThe number of abortions in Jersey has
OL,11,Falso reached its highest level since
OL,12,F2002.
OL,14,FApproximately 260 pregnancy
OL,15,Fterminations were recorded in 2023,
OL,16,Faccording to a report by Public Health.
OL,18,FDepartment Director, Professor Peter
OL,19,FBradley, adds: "We have seen a steady
OL,20,Fdecline in the number of babies born
OL,21,Fin Jersey over the last decade.
